<br>
On my first Linksys router, I went LD every 10 minutes. Set the DMZ setting, it worked fine. <br>
<br>
That router eventually broke, and I returned it. On the second one I went LD every 10 minutes. Set the DMZ setting, it worked fine.<br>
<br>
Two people in the mage channel were going LD with a Linksys router. I told them to set the DMZ, and it worked fine.<br>
<br>
In the Linksys online help it says that if you play online games, then set your DMZ. DMZ DOES MATTER. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=celanxev>CelanXev</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 283<br> <font color=#333333>(2/26/03 9:15:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8898.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re:</span><hr size=1> I have been having new LD problems lately and general lag. I don't think it's the router (probably my cable), but I guess I'll update the firmware.<br>
